{
  "text": "TRFLP patterns of nosZ amplified from DNA were similar in 2008 (drought) and 2009 (flooding) and in both control and treatment plots (P > 0.2; Figures 3C,D) . The five most prominent TRFs were indicative of uncultured soil organisms related to Bradyrhizobiaceae of FEN CLUSTER 1 and Rhodospirillaceae of FEN CLUSTERS 3-5 within the Alphaproteobacteria [CITATION_1] (Figures S3A,B,E,F) .",
